					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Asha Dore</h4>
												<p>Asha Dore is a journalist, illustrator, and speech-language pathologist. Her work has recently appeared in <em>Vogue</em>, <em>Washington Post, New York Magazine, Gulf Coast</em><em>,</em> <em>The Guardian</em>, and elsewhere. Asha is the host of the literary interview podcast, <em><a href="http://www.totallybiasedreviews.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://www.totallybiasedreviews.com/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1768429512852000&amp;usg=AOvVaw2CferGM_vMOEmdCrGsV1w5" class="external">Totally Biased Reviews</a>. </em>Find her at <a href="http://www.ashadore.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://www.AshaDore.net&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1768429512852000&amp;usg=AOvVaw2dstJ3ezBIfO2oZDv1zyBm" class="external">www.AshaDore.net</a> and on Instagram <a href="https://www.instagram.com/adjsbb/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.instagram.com/adjsbb/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1768429512852000&amp;usg=AOvVaw2P7IbJRZhvtbl6foCRd35K" class="external">@adjsbb</a>. She is working on a memoir about crime and class in Florida.</p>
